<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Locality records for Leptonetela trispinosa comb. nov., Leptonetela unispinosa comb. nov. and Leptoneta monodactyla." , "Figure 3. Leptoneta monodactyla Yin et al., 1984, holotype male A right palp (show the whole situation from patella to tarsus, but palpal bulb is missing), retrolateral view B palpal blub, ventral view C right chelicera (because teeth of left chelicera are broken), retrolateral view. Abbreviations: Co, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis." , "Figure 2. Leptoneta monodactyla Yin et al., 1984, Palp of holotype male A prolateral view B retrolateral view. Abbreviations: PL, prolateral lobe; TA, tibial apophysis." , "Figure 1. Leptoneta monodactyla Yin et al., 1984, holotype male A habitus, dorsal view B palpal bulb, ventral view C right palp (show the whole situation from patella to tarsus, but palpal bulb is missing), retrolateral view D palp, prolateral view E palp, retrolateral view." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/482836" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/482830" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/482829" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/482828" .

